commit message: Added mail prefix option and Droid X bug info translation.
Added code to allow backup of call log entries to own label/folder
Fixed bug when contact was found but had no email. In that case the address would always be unknown_number@unknown_email even though the number was known
Handle callers without callerid so they display as 'Unknown'
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/dicer/sms-backup-plus into call-log
Document and credit call log support
Only list 3 most recent releases in about dialog
Mention that MMS is Android 2.x feature

Move buttons to separate column

This is needed to make more space for the status label,
some localizations have more text there.
Only create call log backup folder if needed
Language file update for call logs backup.
Fixed bug where calllog label was not checked and pref label wasn't updated

Added new datatype header to email message. This makes it possible to distinguish between SMS/MMS/calllog when restoring. Also changed restore code to be fully backward compatible. Except for calllog entries which have been backed up until this commit! Since there shouldn't be any real users using the preliminary calllog build the only fix is to delete those calllog backups and back them up again (now with correct headers)
Merge branch 'master' of http://github.com/dicer/sms-backup-plus into call-log
Disable call log folder pref if call log is disabled

Lift IMAP folder name restrictions

Closes GH-79
